s a road that Franz had travelled—and all at once Fate remembered and sent in pursuit this practically nameless man who of course knew nothing of his important assignment, and never found out anything about it, as for that matter no one else ever did, not even old Enricht.

“Welcome,” said Dreyer, “sit down.”

The inventor did.

“Well,” asked Dreyer, toying with his favorite pencil.

